Perhaps the worst Potbelly I've ever been to.  I've had three, consecutive bad experiences here over the past two months.  Once, my grilled chicken sandwich was *ice* cold because I guess they turned off the oven at 5pm.  Another time, an employee was incredible rude to me.  And finally, more recently, an employee messed up what I asked for on my sandwich.  I saw her mistake as she was making it and asked repeatedly for her to put tomatoes on the sandwich.  She, however, was too busy having a conversation about with a co-worker to hear me.  When she handed my sandwich I told her once more that she missed the tomatoes, and she gave me attitude about putting them on again.  I definitely would not recommend this particular location.  There are better run Potbelly's just a few blocks away.

Around any corner in the Loop you are bound to find a Potbelly... The reson I like Potbelly is due to the fact that you are getting a quallity sandwich or salad for a fair price. This is far superior to Jimmy Johns of Subway.. everything is better toasted. This location in particular can improve on their communication with people who order a salad like myself. When the Potbelly employee is taking your order on the tablet to speed up the process of gettting your daily lunch fuel and you order a salad... you do not need to stand in the sandwich wrap line. Go straight to the register for salad pick up and pay for your meal! One thing that I would like to see at the Potbelly would be for online ordering. This would enable me to add one more star to give this place a 5/5!! Overall if you are looking for a fast option for lunch, you can never go wrong with a Wreck and an Oreo shake with mini butter cookies in the middle of the straw. My go to 8/10 times during my visits.
